
\section{Creating your own settings}
I tend to want the same, or similar, settings on most plots, and
"pgfplots" makes it easy to create and use these.  From the manual
``Use "\pgfplotsset{"$\langle\emph{key}\rangle$%
  "/.style = {"$\langle\emph{key-value-list}\rangle$"}}" to (re)define
a style $\langle\emph{key}\rangle$ in the namespace "/pgfplots".''

What this mean is you can do something like this:
\begin{latex}
% probably in preamble 
"\pgfplotsset{
  duckplot/.style={thick,blue,smooth},
  duckaxis/.style={axis lines = middle, xlabel={$x$}, ylabel={$y$}}
}"
% in main document
\begin{tikzpicture}
\begin{axis}"[duckaxis]"
\addplot"[duckplot]"{x^2};
\end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{latex}
and then use that in plots
\pgfplotsset{
duckplot/.style={thick,blue,smooth},
duckaxis/.style={axis lines = middle, xlabel={$x$}, ylabel={$y$}}
}
\begin{center}
\tikzcount
\begin{tikzpicture}
\begin{axis}[duckaxis]
\addplot[duckplot]{x^2};
\end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

You can also change the default settings so you don't need to use
options "duckaxis" and "duckplot" in the above commands.

\begingroup
\begin{latex}
% probably in preamble
\pgfplotsset{
  "every axis/.style" = {axis lines = middle},
  "cycle list name = color list",
  "every axis plot/.style" = {thick,smooth}
}

% in main document
\begin{tikzpicture}
\begin{axis}[restrict y to domain = -5:20]
\addplot{x^2};
\addplot{-2*(x+1)+1};
\addplot{2*(x-1)+1};
\addplot{4*(x-2)+4};
\end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{latex}
% probably in preamble
\pgfplotsset{every axis/.style = {axis lines = middle},
cycle list name = color list,
every axis plot/.style = {thick,smooth}}
\begin{center}
\tikzcount
\begin{tikzpicture}
\begin{axis}[restrict y to domain = -5:20]
\addplot{x^2};
\addplot{-2*(x+1)+1};
\addplot{2*(x-1)+1};
\addplot{4*(x-2)+4};
\end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}
\endgroup




